body:
It seems like this issue might be related to code signing :no_entry_sign:

Have you seen our new [Code Signing Troubleshooting Guide](https://docs.fastlane.tools/codesigning/getting-started/)? It will help you resolve the most common code signing issues :+1:

@acegreen, while I look into this, it might be a great opportunity to migrate from the Fabric Mac App over to one of our better supported install methods: https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/issues/11586

issue.title: Missing variable fix for socket_server

repository.name: fastlane

issue.body:
fixes #11614

If your exception has a `cause` then when we're examining it, we accidentally call `backtrace` instead of `e.backtrace`. `backtrace` isn't a thing.
